243
00:13:57.963 --> 00:13:59.256
are you all right?

244
00:14:00.966 --> 00:14:02.717
No. I'm not.

245
00:14:04.970 --> 00:14:08.223
He had WD-40 in the back.
so I wiped down all the porous surfaces.

246
00:14:08.306 --> 00:14:10.559
They'll be too smudged
to lift any latent prints.

247
00:14:12.143 --> 00:14:15.230
- Podcasts.
- Podcasts.

248
00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:18.817
How long is this train
gonna take?

249
00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:20.402
Should take eight to nine hours.

250
00:14:20.485 --> 00:14:22.779
We'll get to Billy Donovan by tonight.

251
00:14:25.448 --> 00:14:26.950
Come on.

252
00:14:29.911 --> 00:14:31.037
<i>Suivant.</i>

253
00:14:31.121 --> 00:14:34.541
Uh. hi. Could we get. um. two tickets
for the next train to Barcelona. please?

254
00:14:34.624 --> 00:14:38.044
Next train to Barcelona...

255
00:14:38.128 --> 00:14:41.131
leaves at 5:00 p.m.

256
00:14:41.214 --> 00:14:42.632
Not till 5:00?

257
00:14:42.716 --> 00:14:44.634
Wait. Do... do you not have
anything earlier?

258
00:14:44.718 --> 00:14:48.888
The Royal Andalusian Express leaves in...

259
00:14:48.972 --> 00:14:50.390
20 minutes.

260
00:14:50.473 --> 00:14:53.476
Oh. yeah. Yeah. Great. Do two of those.

261
00:14:53.560 --> 00:14:56.438
The only tickets left are
in the First Class sleeper carriage.

262
00:14:57.939 --> 00:15:00.525
The price is...

263
00:15:00.609 --> 00:15:03.820
- Are you insane?
- Is-is this euro or yen or...?

264
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:04.738
Each.

265
00:15:05.572 --> 00:15:06.948
Each?!

266
00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:09.618
That's the next train.
or you can wait until 5:00.

267
00:15:09.701 --> 00:15:13.705
- Yeah. no. We'll take two. Yeah.
- Yeah. Two.

268
00:15:29.179 --> 00:15:31.765
Good grief.

269
00:15:33.099 --> 00:15:34.392
Oh.

270
00:15:35.894 --> 00:15:37.479
That's an antique railroad light.

271
00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:39.439
Oh!

272
00:15:39.522 --> 00:15:41.316
This is Marquina marble.

273
00:15:41.399 --> 00:15:43.485
It's so beautiful.

274
00:15:43.568 --> 00:15:45.195
Ooh!

275
00:15:45.278 --> 00:15:47.322
Ooh. Oh.

276
00:15:47.405 --> 00:15:49.282
A French Baroque inkwell.

277
00:15:50.533 --> 00:15:52.243
Shall I take a letter?

278
00:15:52.327 --> 00:15:54.871
- Yes. take a letter for me. young lady.
- Ooh.

279
00:15:56.039 --> 00:15:57.957
Look at that.

280
00:15:58.041 --> 00:15:59.250
It's crystal.

281
00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:04.756
- Oh.
- Ah.

282
00:16:11.179 --> 00:16:16.726
This was a very financially irresponsible.
but excellent move.

283
00:16:22.315 --> 00:16:24.818
- Oh.
- Oh. my gosh.

284
00:16:32.784 --> 00:16:33.952
Deb.

285
00:16:34.035 --> 00:16:36.037
What's-what's... what's wrong?

286
00:16:36.121 --> 00:16:37.789
I don't know.

287
00:16:37.872 --> 00:16:40.333
It's like. every time I look at you.
I forget.

288
00:16:41.418 --> 00:16:44.462
I want to tell you about this insane thing
that happened to me.

289
00:16:46.423 --> 00:16:48.341
And it's you.

290
00:16:48.425 --> 00:16:50.844
You're the insane thing
that happened to me.

291
00:16:50.927 --> 00:16:53.263
I need to think about something else.

292
00:16:53.346 --> 00:16:55.557
I don't want to think about you or David.

293
00:16:55.640 --> 00:16:57.559
or finding Billy Donovan.

294
00:16:57.642 --> 00:17:02.605
You know what? Give me that. uh.
horrible pirate code thing.

295
00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.693
- This?
- Yeah.

296
00:17:10.447 --> 00:17:12.031
Who is she?

297
00:17:13.116 --> 00:17:14.659
This Judith?

298
00:17:14.743 --> 00:17:17.078
She stopped a war.

299
00:17:18.163 --> 00:17:23.209
There was this Assyrian general
called Holofernes.

300
00:17:23.293 --> 00:17:25.211
and he wanted to destroy her city.

301
00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:28.590
So she snuck into his tent. got him drunk

302
00:17:28.673 --> 00:17:30.633
and cut his head off.

303
00:17:31.885 --> 00:17:35.013
She was the first ever female assassin.

304
00:17:35.096 --> 00:17:38.433
And you chose your name because of her?

305
00:17:38.516 --> 00:17:40.935
Yeah. I suppose.

306
00:17:41.019 --> 00:17:44.939
So this is someone who really knows you.

307
00:17:45.023 --> 00:17:46.566
and they want
to let you know they're coming.

308
00:17:46.649 --> 00:17:48.443
Yeah. all right.

309
00:17:48.526 --> 00:17:51.946
I'm fully aware
that I have lots of enemies.

310
00:17:52.030 --> 00:17:54.657
Oh. I don't think it's an enemy.

311
00:17:54.741 --> 00:17:57.202
I think it's a lover.

312
00:17:57.285 --> 00:17:59.454
I think you broke his heart.

313
00:17:59.537 --> 00:18:02.457
What about someone who loved you?

314
00:18:02.540 --> 00:18:04.292
Oh. that's easy.

315
00:18:04.375 --> 00:18:06.044
There's no one like that.

316
00:18:06.127 --> 00:18:08.213
I've never...

317
00:18:08.296 --> 00:18:11.132
known anyone long enough
for someone to love me.

318
00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:14.427
I loved you.

319
00:18:16.888 --> 00:18:18.264
You broke my heart.

320
00:18:28.817 --> 00:18:30.985
Queenie. I need your help.

321
00:18:31.069 --> 00:18:32.320
With what?

322
00:18:32.403 --> 00:18:34.155
That giant hickey on your neck?

323
00:18:34.239 --> 00:18:36.491
What? No! No.

324
00:18:36.574 --> 00:18:40.453
I've. um... I've misplaced a body.

325
00:18:40.537 --> 00:18:42.956
And not just any body.

326
00:18:43.581 --> 00:18:44.874
An MP.

327
00:18:44.958 --> 00:18:47.460
An MP?

328
00:18:47.544 --> 00:18:49.128
You lost an MP?

329
00:18:49.212 --> 00:18:51.047
Well. I guess you're dead.

330
00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:52.924
Yeah. I know. That's why I'm here.

331
00:18:53.007 --> 00:18:54.342
He was last seen in a hotel room.

332
00:18:54.425 --> 00:18:55.844
And what am I supposed to do about it?

333
00:18:55.927 --> 00:18:57.470
Okay. um...

334
00:18:57.554 --> 00:19:01.850
Do you have a gadget
that can un-erase CCTV footage?

335
00:19:01.933 --> 00:19:03.935
Of course not. you idiot.
What would be the point

336
00:19:04.018 --> 00:19:07.605
of erasing it if you could un-erase it?
No. Wait.

337
00:19:07.689 --> 00:19:12.235
But. I mean. I do have a number
of devices that can kill you.

338
00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:15.613
You know. if you want to take matters
into your own hands. that is.

339
00:19:15.697 --> 00:19:17.365
- Help me find this fucking body.
- Why should I?

340
00:19:17.448 --> 00:19:20.451
Because I'll... I'll owe you.

341
00:19:20.535 --> 00:19:22.495
I'll-I'll be in your debt.

342
00:19:23.621 --> 00:19:26.457
Okay. Well. what are you offering me?

343
00:19:26.541 --> 00:19:28.001
Wh-What do you want?

344
00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:29.627
I don't know yet.

345
00:19:29.711 --> 00:19:30.795
Okay. fine. Um...

346
00:19:30.879 --> 00:19:32.964
- Sam! Hello. luv.
- Hi. Hi.

347
00:19:33.047 --> 00:19:35.592
- What are you doing here?
- Sam got laid. Mum.

348
00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:38.511
- Oh. well done.
- No. that's not true.

349
00:19:39.596 --> 00:19:41.723
I... Well. I mean. yeah. I did.

350
00:19:41.806 --> 00:19:45.393
but I'm... I'm here because Queenie

351
00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:48.813
<i>has graciously offered to help me clean up
a previous Whiptail disaster.</i>

352
00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:50.398
<i>so I can work on her current disaster.</i>

353
00:19:50.481 --> 00:19:53.276
<i>- And now she's God-knows-where in France.
- I'm tracking her passport.</i>

354
00:19:53.359 --> 00:19:55.069
<i>She's at Calais train station.</i>

355
00:19:55.153 --> 00:19:58.364
<i>What? Jesus Christ.
What is she doing on a train?</i>

356
00:20:01.743 --> 00:20:03.328
<i>She's at Calais train station.</i>

357
00:20:47.080 --> 00:20:49.248
Afternoon. ladies.

358
00:20:49.332 --> 00:20:52.418
Can I get you started
with one of our fresh peach Bellinis?

359
00:20:52.502 --> 00:20:54.212
Uh. just a water. thank you.

360
00:20:54.295 --> 00:20:57.006
- Uh. two. please.
- One.

361
00:20:57.090 --> 00:20:58.466
Two peach Bellinis.

362
00:20:58.549 --> 00:21:00.593
And what name should I put on the tab?

363
00:21:00.677 --> 00:21:02.136
De...

364
00:21:02.220 --> 00:21:05.306
Veronica. I am Veronica Gillingsby.

365
00:21:05.390 --> 00:21:08.393
I'm a normal British woman
with no problems.

366
00:21:08.476 --> 00:21:10.395
- Well. okay.
- Mm.

367
00:21:10.478 --> 00:21:11.938
Veronica. is it?

368
00:21:12.021 --> 00:21:13.106
- Mm.
- Nice to meet you both.

369
00:21:13.189 --> 00:21:14.941
Where are you two headed?

370
00:21:15.024 --> 00:21:16.442
Uh. Rome.

371
00:21:16.526 --> 00:21:19.862
Rome? On a train heading to Seville?

372
00:21:21.698 --> 00:21:25.743
Well. of course to Seville.
and then on to Rome.

373
00:21:25.827 --> 00:21:28.705
We-we have to get to a... a meeting.

374
00:21:30.289 --> 00:21:31.541
- We've just been to Rome.
- Christ.

375
00:21:33.042 --> 00:21:35.128
Loved it. But where's your meeting at?

376
00:21:35.211 --> 00:21:37.171
The Vatican.

377
00:21:37.255 --> 00:21:38.297
- The Vatican?
- Mm.

378
00:21:38.381 --> 00:21:39.757
Darling.

379
00:21:39.841 --> 00:21:43.052
what sort of business do you have
at the Vatican?

380
00:21:43.136 --> 00:21:45.430
Or is it just simply too vulgar to ask?

381
00:21:45.513 --> 00:21:47.682
No. no. not at all.

382
00:21:47.765 --> 00:21:49.434
Not at all.

383
00:21:49.517 --> 00:21:52.854
Uh. just a brief discussion about...

384
00:21:52.937 --> 00:21:54.522
AI.

385
00:21:56.107 --> 00:21:57.942
I would love to hear
from someone that truly knows

386
00:21:58.026 --> 00:22:01.779
- what is Artificial Intelligence.
- Yes. Quite.

387
00:22:01.863 --> 00:22:03.197
- Yes. quite.
- Quite.

388
00:22:03.281 --> 00:22:05.324
Indeed.

389
00:22:05.408 --> 00:22:07.827
Indeed.

390
00:22:09.120 --> 00:22:10.705
<i>Okay. first.
let's see if David Claybourne</i>

391
00:22:10.788 --> 00:22:13.875
even was in this hotel room.

392
00:22:13.958 --> 00:22:17.378
Well. if he was. these glasses
will detect any trace of DNA.

393
00:22:19.464 --> 00:22:21.215
New carpet?

394
00:22:21.299 --> 00:22:24.052
Yeah. Yeah.
Um. cost more than the job paid.

395
00:22:28.222 --> 00:22:31.350
Well. genuinely. you did too good a job.

396
00:22:31.434 --> 00:22:34.020
'cause there's nothing here.

397
00:22:36.606 --> 00:22:38.816
It was a long shot.

398
00:22:38.900 --> 00:22:42.695
Sorry for...
dragging you all the way out here.

399
00:22:47.492 --> 00:22:48.659
Wait.

400
00:22:51.287 --> 00:22:52.789
There's spots of blood on here.

401
00:22:53.873 --> 00:22:56.042
You said the bodies
were all put in bags. right?

402
00:22:56.125 --> 00:22:58.628
Water-sealant cadaver pouches. yeah.

403
00:22:58.711 --> 00:23:01.714
So why would there be blood
outside the door?

404
00:23:01.798 --> 00:23:04.550
I mean. unless...

405
00:23:04.634 --> 00:23:07.637
A body was moved before we got here.

406
00:23:10.598 --> 00:23:12.767
There's more out here.

407
00:23:14.977 --> 00:23:15.978
Indentation in the carpet.

408
00:23:16.062 --> 00:23:17.897
Maybe they used a-a luggage cart thing.

409
00:23:22.401 --> 00:23:23.402
Um...

410
00:23:27.156 --> 00:23:29.659
Definitely big enough to fit a body.

411
00:23:29.742 --> 00:23:31.536
Where do you think it goes?

412
00:23:31.619 --> 00:23:33.079
Let's find out.

413
00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:34.997
Queenie.

414
00:23:35.081 --> 00:23:36.624
- I'll see you on the other side.
- No.

415
00:23:36.707 --> 00:23:38.960
Queenie! Queenie!

416
00:24:18.583 --> 00:24:20.209
Motherfuckers.

417
00:24:25.089 --> 00:24:27.633
<i>So. here I am
three days up Mount Everest.</i>

418
00:24:27.717 --> 00:24:29.135
<i>And I say to my Sherpa...</i>

419
00:24:29.218 --> 00:24:31.053
His name was Sanu.

420
00:24:31.137 --> 00:24:34.015
Oh. we're still extremely close friends.

421
00:24:34.098 --> 00:24:37.602
"I simply cannot climb another inch."

422
00:24:37.685 --> 00:24:39.395
And he said to me.

423
00:24:39.478 --> 00:24:41.272
"Open your eyes.

424
00:24:41.355 --> 00:24:43.774
You're already at the top."

425
00:24:45.443 --> 00:24:46.736
I was already there.

426
00:24:46.819 --> 00:24:48.738
Who wants another round?

427
00:24:48.821 --> 00:24:52.366
François. another round of Bellinis
for me and my friends.

428
00:24:52.450 --> 00:24:53.576
Thank you.

429
00:24:55.453 --> 00:24:57.246
You're being ridiculous.

430
00:24:57.330 --> 00:24:59.081
I know.

431
00:24:59.165 --> 00:25:01.667
I know I'm being ridiculous.

432
00:25:01.751 --> 00:25:03.586
I also know that when this train stops.

433
00:25:03.669 --> 00:25:05.421
I got to get off and go back
to being Debbie Claybourne.

434
00:25:05.504 --> 00:25:08.174
and she has to call her children

435
00:25:08.257 --> 00:25:10.551
and tell them their father's dead.

436
00:25:11.719 --> 00:25:16.557
So. for a few hours.
I would really like to be someone else.

437
00:25:16.641 --> 00:25:19.185
I would like to be ridiculous.

438
00:25:19.268 --> 00:25:22.813
And I would really appreciate it
if you would be ridiculous with me.

439
00:25:26.901 --> 00:25:30.488
François. I'm gonna need a Bellini.

440
00:25:30.571 --> 00:25:32.240
<i>So.</i>

441
00:25:32.323 --> 00:25:35.201
we're outside Dar es Salaam.
car broken down.

442
00:25:35.284 --> 00:25:36.410
Middle of the Serengeti.

443
00:25:36.494 --> 00:25:38.037
And there we was.

444
00:25:38.120 --> 00:25:42.416
A lion. Staring at us. face to face.

445
00:25:42.500 --> 00:25:45.461
And he comes at me...

446
00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:49.840
and Veronica whips out her weapon and...

447
00:25:49.924 --> 00:25:52.134
I sang to it.

448
00:25:52.218 --> 00:25:56.138
Because violence is never the answer.

449
00:25:56.847 --> 00:25:58.099
And slowly.

450
00:25:58.182 --> 00:26:01.352
ever so slowly.
the lion laid down at my feet.

451
00:26:01.435 --> 00:26:03.020
That's incredible.

452
00:26:03.104 --> 00:26:06.107
That's quite a life you have lived.
Veronica. Both of you.

453
00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:10.486
In Prague. we have an expression.
<i>Bez práce...</i>

454
00:26:10.569 --> 00:26:12.405
<i>Nesjou kolace.</i>

455
00:26:12.989 --> 00:26:14.115
You speak Czech?

456
00:26:14.198 --> 00:26:15.241
Mm...

457
00:26:15.324 --> 00:26:16.158
A little.

458
00:26:16.867 --> 00:26:19.745
- Oh...
- Yes. when I was a young girl.

459
00:26:19.829 --> 00:26:22.665
I would spend all my summers
at my aunt's house

460
00:26:22.748 --> 00:26:25.376
just outside of Karlovy Vary.

461
00:26:25.459 --> 00:26:27.044
I used to love...

462
00:26:27.128 --> 00:26:28.671
Scavenging for mushrooms.

463
00:26:28.754 --> 00:26:32.466
Yes. That's right.
I. um... I told you that.

464
00:26:34.510 --> 00:26:36.804
And I even met your aunt.

465
00:26:38.055 --> 00:26:39.181
Yes.

466
00:26:39.265 --> 00:26:41.142
But it wasn't your real aunt.

467
00:26:43.185 --> 00:26:47.898
Yeah. well.
she was a very close friend of the family.

468
00:26:47.982 --> 00:26:49.442
And you didn't really scavenge
for mushrooms.

469
00:26:49.525 --> 00:26:50.818
This isn't fun anymore.

470
00:26:50.901 --> 00:26:52.278
Wait. What?

471
00:26:53.529 --> 00:26:55.197
What are you doing?

472
00:26:55.281 --> 00:26:58.159
I did this for a brief escape.

473
00:26:58.242 --> 00:26:59.744
making up stories.

474
00:26:59.827 --> 00:27:02.455
but your whole life is made-up stories.

475
00:27:02.538 --> 00:27:03.998
I don't really know anything about you.

476
00:27:04.081 --> 00:27:05.875
Yes. you do.

477
00:27:05.958 --> 00:27:07.585
More than anyone.

478
00:27:22.266 --> 00:27:27.104
So... there's no aunt in Karlovy Vary?

479
00:27:38.616 --> 00:27:41.452
For you and your friend.

480
00:27:42.912 --> 00:27:44.830
From the gentlemen at the bar.

481
00:28:11.482 --> 00:28:12.691
<i>Queenie!</i>

482
00:28:13.901 --> 00:28:15.236
Queenie?

483
00:28:18.114 --> 00:28:20.866
Yeah. it stops here. End of the trail.

484
00:28:20.950 --> 00:28:23.661
I'm not picking up
any more traces of blood.

485
00:28:24.328 --> 00:28:27.206
- Now what?
- Now.

486
00:28:27.289 --> 00:28:29.792
I need two Mini Cheddars. a Cherryade.

487
00:28:29.875 --> 00:28:32.002
a Wispa Duo and...

488
00:28:32.086 --> 00:28:34.130
- a pack of Skittles.
- Queenie.

489
00:28:34.213 --> 00:28:37.883
And the time it takes me to eat them
is exactly how long it will take me

490
00:28:37.967 --> 00:28:41.554
to download the security camera
from that ATM.

491
00:28:41.637 --> 00:28:43.389
Oh. my God. I love you.

492
00:28:44.473 --> 00:28:47.268
As in... just you're amazing.

493
00:28:48.561 --> 00:28:50.354
I know. Sam.

494
00:28:50.438 --> 00:28:51.564
I know.

495
00:29:05.786 --> 00:29:06.996
Hmm.

496
00:29:54.251 --> 00:29:56.212
Debbie?

497
00:29:59.465 --> 00:30:01.133
Debbie cries.

498
00:30:03.719 --> 00:30:05.304
Veronica doesn't.

499
00:30:31.455 --> 00:30:33.123
Debbie?

500
00:30:33.207 --> 00:30:35.543
Debbie!

501
00:30:46.095 --> 00:30:48.430
Uh. s-sorry. Was this your seat?

502
00:30:48.514 --> 00:30:50.307
No. No. it's all right.

503
00:30:50.391 --> 00:30:53.102
Please join me.
Unless you are waiting for someone?

504
00:30:53.185 --> 00:30:55.396
- No. It's just me.
- Please.

505
00:30:55.479 --> 00:30:59.692
I just have some trinkets.
you know. for-for my grandkids.

506
00:30:59.775 --> 00:31:01.110
Aw.

507
00:31:01.193 --> 00:31:05.114
I couldn't help
but overhear some of your travels.

508
00:31:05.864 --> 00:31:08.617
Uh. the lions in the Serengeti.

509
00:31:08.701 --> 00:31:10.536
Uh. the meeting with the Pope.

510
00:31:10.619 --> 00:31:14.999
Yeah. I may have taken a few liberties.

511
00:31:15.082 --> 00:31:17.084
But something tells me

512
00:31:17.167 --> 00:31:22.631
that your real story
might be even more exciting.

513
00:31:22.715 --> 00:31:27.678
It's quite... complicated.

514
00:31:27.761 --> 00:31:29.638
All the best stories are.

515
00:31:45.529 --> 00:31:47.740
Hydroxybutyric acid.

516
00:31:49.533 --> 00:31:52.494
Faster than a roofie
and stays in your system longer.

517
00:31:52.578 --> 00:31:54.371
Getting Mickey-Finn'ed in a bar car.

518
00:31:55.998 --> 00:31:58.167
- You know better than that. Whiptail.
- How do you...?

519
00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:00.961
How do you know my...?

520
00:32:01.045 --> 00:32:03.088
Why are you following me?

521
00:32:03.172 --> 00:32:05.382
You sent me the postcards?

522
00:32:05.466 --> 00:32:06.884
You sent

523
00:32:06.967 --> 00:32:09.094
the postcards and the Black Mark!

524
00:32:09.178 --> 00:32:11.055
No. I didn't send any postcards.
That sounds fucking lame.

525
00:32:11.138 --> 00:32:13.682
- No.
- You got the wrong guy. luv.

526
00:32:13.766 --> 00:32:15.309
I'm not even here for you.

527
00:32:15.392 --> 00:32:17.019
Don't get me wrong.

528
00:32:17.102 --> 00:32:19.605
I'd love a shot at you.

529
00:32:19.688 --> 00:32:21.398
but you're not the job.

530
00:32:21.482 --> 00:32:23.192
One Mrs. Deborah Claybourne.

531
00:32:23.275 --> 00:32:26.153
What? Debbie?

532
00:32:26.236 --> 00:32:27.738
No. Why?

533
00:32:27.821 --> 00:32:29.782
She phoned the police.

534
00:32:29.865 --> 00:32:31.325
Told them about our mutual employer.

535
00:32:31.408 --> 00:32:33.494
You know the rules.

536
00:32:33.577 --> 00:32:36.205
He sent you? The Director sent you?

537
00:32:36.288 --> 00:32:37.873
Stop it!

538
00:32:37.956 --> 00:32:39.375
Don't worry about your little friend.

539
00:32:40.459 --> 00:32:42.252
- I'll make it quick.
- No.

540
00:32:42.336 --> 00:32:43.671
No.

541
00:32:46.090 --> 00:32:49.259
So tell me. Ms. Veronica.

542
00:32:49.343 --> 00:32:51.804
Who are you. really?

543
00:32:56.600 --> 00:32:58.018
I don't know anymore.

544
00:32:58.102 --> 00:32:59.269
Hmm.

545
00:33:01.605 --> 00:33:05.693
Three days ago. I had it all mapped out.

546
00:33:05.776 --> 00:33:09.446
Knew who I was. where I was going.

547
00:33:11.073 --> 00:33:14.326
<i>And now. when I look in the mirror.
I don't...</i>

548
00:33:14.410 --> 00:33:15.911
<i>recognize myself.</i>

549
00:33:24.837 --> 00:33:28.757
It feels like I'm in freefall.

550
00:33:29.675 --> 00:33:33.929
<i>Like there's nothing
from my old life to hold on to.</i>

551
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:36.849
<i>and I don't know how long
I'm going to keep falling</i>

552
00:33:36.932 --> 00:33:38.851
<i>or where I'm going to land.</i>

553
00:33:47.901 --> 00:33:49.278
<i>Three days ago.</i>

554
00:33:49.361 --> 00:33:53.157
my whole world was turned upside down.

555
00:34:07.212 --> 00:34:11.884
Two of the people I loved most
in the world...

556
00:34:11.967 --> 00:34:13.594
lied to me.

557
00:34:19.308 --> 00:34:24.021
<i>I suppose we are all liars
in our own way.</i>

558
00:34:28.275 --> 00:34:31.695
The truth is a tough place to live.

559
00:34:31.779 --> 00:34:33.614
We don't lie to those we love.

560
00:34:33.697 --> 00:34:35.324
Don't we?

561
00:34:36.283 --> 00:34:38.869
<i>From my experience.
we lie to them the most.</i>

562
00:34:52.466 --> 00:34:54.426
I lied. Whiptail.

563
00:34:54.510 --> 00:34:57.805
I'm not gonna kill your friend fast.

564
00:34:57.888 --> 00:35:01.099
I'm gonna take my time.

565
00:35:01.183 --> 00:35:02.559
I'm gonna make it hurt.

566
00:35:08.023 --> 00:35:12.236
<i>Some people lie.
not in spite of their love for you.</i>

567
00:35:12.319 --> 00:35:14.029
but because of it.

568
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:17.032
Because they want to protect you.
no matter what.

569
00:35:20.077 --> 00:35:22.037
Goodbye. Whiptail.

570
00:35:46.603 --> 00:35:49.940
Judith! Your head is bleeding.
What-what happened?

571
00:35:50.023 --> 00:35:51.733
- Got to go now.
- What?

572
00:35:52.776 --> 00:35:53.777
Judith.

573
00:35:53.861 --> 00:35:56.363
What are you doing?

574
00:35:56.446 --> 00:35:58.198
Why are you opening the door?

575
00:35:59.491 --> 00:36:01.285
Judith. talk to me!

576
00:36:01.368 --> 00:36:02.578
Listen to me!

577
00:36:02.661 --> 00:36:04.580
They know that we're on the train.
and there's gonna be

578
00:36:04.663 --> 00:36:06.081
other people waiting for us
at the station.

579
00:36:06.164 --> 00:36:08.000
- Who are they?
- People from my world.

580
00:36:08.083 --> 00:36:10.794
They found us. Okay?

581
00:36:10.878 --> 00:36:12.921
Our window of opportunity is closing.

582
00:36:13.005 --> 00:36:15.048
We have to get off now.

583
00:36:15.132 --> 00:36:16.508
What do you mean get off? You mean jump?

584
00:36:16.592 --> 00:36:19.595
The train has to slow down
at the next curve.

585
00:36:19.678 --> 00:36:21.555
and then it's gonna speed up.

586
00:36:21.638 --> 00:36:23.682
If we wait. we'll have very little chance
of survival.

587
00:36:23.765 --> 00:36:25.392
What are our chances now?

588
00:36:25.475 --> 00:36:27.227
A lot less if we stay on the train.

589
00:36:29.479 --> 00:36:31.523
If we stay on the train. we're gonna die.

590
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:33.317
Okay?

591
00:36:38.697 --> 00:36:39.990
- This is it. this is our window.
- Oh! Oh!

592
00:36:40.073 --> 00:36:41.074
You've got it. It's okay.

593
00:36:41.158 --> 00:36:42.618
You can do this.

594
00:36:42.701 --> 00:36:45.537
I can't. It's going too fast!

595
00:36:45.621 --> 00:36:47.789
Veronica can do this.

596
00:36:50.000 --> 00:36:51.585
No.

597
00:36:51.668 --> 00:36:53.462
Debbie can do this.

598
00:37:06.308 --> 00:37:08.644
Debbie!

599
00:37:11.229 --> 00:37:13.649
Ah. Slow. slow. slow.

600
00:37:13.732 --> 00:37:17.152
Are you all right?
Just take it easy. take it easy.

601
00:37:17.235 --> 00:37:19.404
I'm alive.

602
00:37:19.488 --> 00:37:22.449
Oh. I feel incredible!

603
00:37:23.575 --> 00:37:26.036
I just jumped from a moving train
and I'm alive!

604
00:37:26.119 --> 00:37:28.121
She's alive!

605
00:37:31.208 --> 00:37:32.751
We're alive. Judith!

606
00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:40.258
Oh...

607
00:37:40.342 --> 00:37:42.552
- Ooh. Oh.
- Ugh.

608
00:37:44.805 --> 00:37:46.014
- Oh...
- Oh...

609
00:37:48.850 --> 00:37:51.770
Son of a bitch.

610
00:37:52.896 --> 00:37:57.067
Son of a bitch.
How could I have been so stupid?

611
00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:58.694
Uh. what?

612
00:37:58.777 --> 00:38:00.737
All the metaphors and that lovely hat!

613
00:38:00.821 --> 00:38:03.323
Wait. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
What are you talking about?

614
00:38:04.992 --> 00:38:07.035
We've been robbed.

615
00:38:08.120 --> 00:38:09.121
What?

616
00:38:09.204 --> 00:38:10.789
- We've been robbed.
- No. no. no. no.

617
00:38:10.872 --> 00:38:12.624
No!

618
00:38:12.708 --> 00:38:16.503
Debbie. uh. where-where are our passports?

619
00:38:16.586 --> 00:38:19.131
Debbie. where are our passports or the...

620
00:38:19.214 --> 00:38:24.011
Where's all the money?
Where's all the money? What the...?

621
00:38:25.470 --> 00:38:27.014
Debbie!

622
00:38:27.097 --> 00:38:29.766
- Oh. no. no!
- Goddamn it!

623
00:38:31.685 --> 00:38:33.603
Fuck!

624
00:38:39.067 --> 00:38:42.112
Maybe now you get it.
You can never let your guard down.

625
00:38:42.195 --> 00:38:44.031
I am well aware.

626
00:38:44.114 --> 00:38:46.366
And the last thing I need
is a lecture from you.

627
00:38:46.450 --> 00:38:48.702
If I could walk any faster
to get away from you. I would.

628
00:38:50.579 --> 00:38:53.206
- Did you just harumph?
- No. it's all in your mind.

629
00:38:53.290 --> 00:38:55.792
Yeah. I made a mistake.

630
00:38:55.876 --> 00:38:57.461
But I'm sorry. I. uh.

631
00:38:57.544 --> 00:38:59.713
have never had to pretend
to be someone else before.

632
00:39:01.757 --> 00:39:03.050
There it is again.

633
00:39:03.759 --> 00:39:05.135
You got something to say?

634
00:39:05.218 --> 00:39:08.722
Say it. Because when this road ends.
so do we.

635
00:39:08.805 --> 00:39:11.141
- You really want me to say it?
- Mm-hmm.

636
00:39:11.224 --> 00:39:13.226
Fine.

637
00:39:13.310 --> 00:39:16.313
You think that your life
isn't about pretending?

638
00:39:16.396 --> 00:39:18.440
All you do is pretend.

639
00:39:18.523 --> 00:39:21.485
You pretend that you're happy.

640
00:39:21.568 --> 00:39:25.405
You pretend that you are
in this loving. trusting relationship.

641
00:39:25.489 --> 00:39:27.699
and that-that you guys are equal.

642
00:39:27.783 --> 00:39:31.536
David has never ever deserved you.

643
00:39:31.620 --> 00:39:35.082
- How dare you? How dare you?
- All of this is the biggest lie.

644
00:39:35.165 --> 00:39:36.917
We were a team.

645
00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:38.502
Oh. bullshit.

646
00:39:38.585 --> 00:39:42.756
No. don't you walk away from me.
You need to hear this.

647
00:39:43.840 --> 00:39:46.635
You always tell everyone that.
when you met him.

648
00:39:46.718 --> 00:39:49.346
you got off the train
because you were so charmed by him.

649
00:39:49.429 --> 00:39:52.265
but David is irrelevant.

650
00:39:52.349 --> 00:39:54.851
I think you got off the train...

651
00:39:54.935 --> 00:39:57.437
because you were too scared
to make it on your own.

652
00:39:58.605 --> 00:40:00.398
Mm. All right.

653
00:40:00.482 --> 00:40:02.609
But what about you. hmm?

654
00:40:03.276 --> 00:40:07.405
You've lived such a-an incredibly
courageous life. is that the idea?

655
00:40:07.489 --> 00:40:08.990
Well. I've never lived it in fear.

656
00:40:09.074 --> 00:40:10.784
- You really believe that?
- Yeah.

657
00:40:10.867 --> 00:40:13.161
You are the most cowardly person
I have ever met.

658
00:40:13.245 --> 00:40:14.496
- Really?
- Really.

659
00:40:14.579 --> 00:40:17.749
- You really think that?
- Mm. I've known you for 25 years.

660
00:40:17.833 --> 00:40:22.003
and in all that time. you haven't had
a single proper romantic relationship.

661
00:40:22.087 --> 00:40:25.298
Oh. so that makes me a coward?
Because I've never settled

662
00:40:25.382 --> 00:40:27.634
- like you did?
- No! No.

663
00:40:27.717 --> 00:40:29.803
It's because you don't want
to be challenged.

664
00:40:29.886 --> 00:40:32.055
You've created this wall of lies

665
00:40:32.139 --> 00:40:33.557
because you're scared of getting hurt.

666
00:40:33.640 --> 00:40:36.351
You don't want anyone to get too close.
because if they do.

667
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:40.188
they just might see the real Judith.
or whatever the hell your name is.

668
00:40:40.272 --> 00:40:43.984
You haven't told me a single
truthful thing since the moment I met you.

669
00:40:44.067 --> 00:40:45.569
I couldn't.

670
00:40:48.363 --> 00:40:49.531
'Cause you would've left me.

671
00:40:49.614 --> 00:40:51.074
You don't know what
I would've done. Judith.

672
00:40:51.158 --> 00:40:53.326
Yes. I do know what you would've done.

673
00:40:53.410 --> 00:40:57.164
You would've done what everyone's done
that's ever got to know the real me.

674
00:40:57.247 --> 00:40:58.832
They all leave.

675
00:41:00.208 --> 00:41:04.546
I don't have anyone. I don't have
any other friendships like this.

676
00:41:04.629 --> 00:41:09.551
I-I... The two
most important things in my life

677
00:41:09.634 --> 00:41:13.555
are you and my job.
and now. I've fucked them both!

678
00:41:13.638 --> 00:41:15.724
So. yes. you're completely right.

679
00:41:15.807 --> 00:41:20.604
I am scared. I'm scared...

680
00:41:20.687 --> 00:41:22.606
I'm so scared I can hardly breathe.

681
00:41:23.690 --> 00:41:25.525
Of what?

682
00:41:28.862 --> 00:41:31.406
I'm terrified to lose you.

683
00:41:36.244 --> 00:41:37.746
See?

684
00:41:37.829 --> 00:41:42.459
I'm terrified that I never
even had you. so...

685
00:41:42.542 --> 00:41:44.669
What?

686
00:41:44.753 --> 00:41:46.171
You've always had me.

687
00:41:49.549 --> 00:41:52.093
- All right. Give me a hug.
- I want to give you a hug.

688
00:41:52.177 --> 00:41:56.348
I'm sorry. I've never been this mean
to anybody in my life.

689
00:41:56.431 --> 00:42:00.060
Well... I have. but not to you.

690
00:42:05.774 --> 00:42:07.525
Oh. my God. it's a fucking truck. Quick.

691
00:42:07.609 --> 00:42:09.903
- Hey!
- Hello. <i>Bonjour. bonjour!</i>

692
00:42:09.986 --> 00:42:12.280
<i>Bonjour!</i> Don't-don't leave.

693
00:42:29.339 --> 00:42:30.382
What's it's on now?

694
00:42:31.424 --> 00:42:32.550
Eighty-nine percent.

695
00:42:32.634 --> 00:42:34.177
One percent more
than when you last asked me.

696
00:42:37.722 --> 00:42:40.850
So. how did you get started at the Agency?

697
00:42:42.269 --> 00:42:43.520
Okay.

698
00:42:43.603 --> 00:42:45.355
When I was. like. 15.

699
00:42:45.438 --> 00:42:48.775
I stole cars.

700
00:42:49.734 --> 00:42:50.944
- Oh!
- Yeah.

701
00:42:51.027 --> 00:42:54.739
Anyway. one night.
I see this BMW parked up.

702
00:42:54.823 --> 00:42:56.741
I break in. I hot-wire it.

703
00:42:56.825 --> 00:42:58.326
I'm about to take off. and then...

704
00:42:59.160 --> 00:43:00.161
Bam!

705
00:43:00.245 --> 00:43:02.747
A body smashed on to the hood.

706
00:43:02.831 --> 00:43:04.457
- Dead?
- Well. I don't know.

707
00:43:04.541 --> 00:43:07.877
So. I open the door. get out.
see if they're okay.

708
00:43:07.961 --> 00:43:11.464
I look down.
and they put a gun in my face.

709
00:43:11.548 --> 00:43:14.592
"Drive." They're directing.

710
00:43:14.676 --> 00:43:18.305
There's sirens going. I'm driving
like a maniac in a stolen bloody car.

711
00:43:18.388 --> 00:43:21.141
And then. next thing I know.
they're going. "Pull over. pull over."

712
00:43:21.224 --> 00:43:24.269
And we're in some middle-of-nowhere.
deserted warehouse.

713
00:43:26.771 --> 00:43:29.107
So. I get out.

714
00:43:29.190 --> 00:43:32.527
Now. there's. like.
five more guns in my face.

715
00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:36.614
and this guy in these overalls goes.
"What'd you want us to do with him?"

716
00:43:38.241 --> 00:43:39.284
She looks at me.

717
00:43:40.827 --> 00:43:41.870
Shrugs.

718
00:43:43.330 --> 00:43:44.748
And says. "Train him up."

719
00:43:45.832 --> 00:43:49.169
- And that was Whiptail?
- Whiptail. Yeah.

720
00:43:49.252 --> 00:43:50.962
And what about The Director?

721
00:43:51.046 --> 00:43:52.297
You know him.

722
00:43:52.380 --> 00:43:55.008
You-you talk to him.
Like. he trusts you.

723
00:43:55.091 --> 00:43:56.468
He must trust you.

724
00:43:56.551 --> 00:43:58.053
Yeah. I guess. Yeah.

725
00:43:58.136 --> 00:44:00.180
Then that's what I want.

726
00:44:00.263 --> 00:44:03.808
In return for helping you.
I-I want a meeting.

727
00:44:03.892 --> 00:44:07.729
Are you joking? I'm hanging on
to my job by a literal thread.

728
00:44:07.812 --> 00:44:10.523
Uh. why not ask your mum?
She knows him better than I do.

729
00:44:10.607 --> 00:44:14.402
I... I don't want my mum to know about it.

730
00:44:17.364 --> 00:44:20.909
Like. about two months ago.
I had to renew my motorcycle license.

731
00:44:20.992 --> 00:44:23.286
and I had to hand in my birth certificate.

732
00:44:23.370 --> 00:44:28.083
So. I go. take it out the drawer. and...

733
00:44:28.166 --> 00:44:29.292
it's a fake.

734
00:44:29.376 --> 00:44:33.088
It's like a really good one.
and that's how I know my mum made it.

735
00:44:33.171 --> 00:44:34.839
but...

736
00:44:34.923 --> 00:44:37.050
I don't know why.

737
00:44:37.133 --> 00:44:41.805
But I think that The Director
might know the truth. so...

738
00:44:41.888 --> 00:44:44.307
that's why I want a meeting.

739
00:44:46.893 --> 00:44:48.103
Okay.

740
00:44:48.186 --> 00:44:50.563
I'll see what I can do.

741
00:44:50.647 --> 00:44:53.358
Okay. Cool.

742
00:44:53.441 --> 00:44:55.151
Cool.

743
00:44:56.403 --> 00:44:57.237
It's done.

744
00:45:36.651 --> 00:45:38.361
<i>Gracias. señor.</i>

745
00:45:45.326 --> 00:45:48.455
I'm... gonna give you some privacy.

746
00:46:04.929 --> 00:46:06.306
Wait. What's that?

747
00:46:09.434 --> 00:46:11.019
There he is.

748
00:46:11.102 --> 00:46:13.438
Hi. sweetheart.

749
00:46:13.521 --> 00:46:15.899
Is your brother with you?

750
00:46:17.650 --> 00:46:19.652
Okay. okay. I...

751
00:46:20.862 --> 00:46:23.114
I have something
very important to tell you both.

752
00:46:23.198 --> 00:46:28.536
I hate to be doing this over the phone.
but I will be with you both very soon.

753
00:46:28.620 --> 00:46:30.497
I promise.

754
00:46:33.124 --> 00:46:34.792
It's about your father.

755
00:46:37.337 --> 00:46:38.505
He's...

756
00:46:41.966 --> 00:46:43.301
Wait.

757
00:46:44.385 --> 00:46:45.386
What?

758
00:46:47.180 --> 00:46:48.806
When?

759
00:47:00.818 --> 00:47:02.153
Damn it.

760
00:47:02.237 --> 00:47:04.155
Okay. can we get any wider?

761
00:47:04.239 --> 00:47:07.492
No. I can't get any wider.
Martin Scorsese.

762
00:47:07.575 --> 00:47:09.285
Back it up.

763
00:47:15.875 --> 00:47:16.960
There. there. Stop.

764
00:47:29.347 --> 00:47:32.183
Oh. fuck.

765
00:47:32.267 --> 00:47:35.603
Honey... I need to call you back.

766
00:47:37.689 --> 00:47:39.274
I love you.

767
00:47:45.363 --> 00:47:46.614
He's alive.

768
00:47:48.032 --> 00:47:49.242
